values: YAY!!!! We are finally DONE with actually attending Prout! I say attending because we are all well aware of the fact that we aren't exactly just going to pick up and walk away, even if some of us say that's what we're gonna do. We'll be in and out over the next little while, I'm sure. Anyway! Yes! I have finally done what my parents, Ms. Hoyt, My other absolutely awesome and favorite teachers (Doc H., Greco,...), and myself especially, have been working towards, and trying to get me to and through. I have officially graduated from The Prout School, Wakefield, RI. Yes! I am now officially an Alumnaieaiaeiaia of the Prout School, and a member of the 37th graduating class, the Class of 2005. But, that's all just a bunch of mumbo-jumbo. A bunch of bullshit. Class this, and school that. I am a member of a family, and together, this family and I, have just finally opened the friggin' door those teachers have been talking about showing to us. Yes, all 115 of us managed to squeeze right on through that door. And now, we start off on our owns in the coming fall season. My family, my whole entire world, my reason for living, my support group, my brothers and sisters, my friends, and my home... they've all just started a very short and quick process of leaving....and of saying good-bye. And While I am so utterly and completely proud, happy, and thrilled with my class and the people in it, the ceaselessly-amazing people of my class, I can't help being sad right now..... I've heard it said before....That some seniors just might not have awakened to the fact that it really is a "Ready or Not!" type of thing....graduation. While it is a wonderful new beginning, and an amazing end to amazing times in your life.....It's heart-wrenching, and "pull the carpet out from under you" at the exact same time! Everything that I am today, All of the people I know and care about and know about and worry about....they're going away....off in new directions, off to live with new people, make new friends, have a new set of classmates, whom will be dubbed "The Class of 2009" in most cases. I....I guess that I'm afraid...... Many of my comforts have been the ability to fall back and depend upon Prout, and my classmates, and the activities, and so forth.......and it bothers me now that all of it is changing.....all of it..... The people are going to change, whether we are ready for it or not, the school is changing, both physically and spiritually ready for it or not, the way we live our lives is about to change completely ready for it or not, and now, many of us will be forced completely out of our comfort zones, be forced to meet new people, be forced into living with some complete stranger in most cases, and in new places, with new ideas, teachers, classes, and EVERYTHING.......ready or not.....here it all comes! And I'm not ready for it all....I'm really not! I can't stand the idea of my family leaving me here in Rhode Island, alone and stuck in my parent's house. Yeah, cuz I'm going to a school where they don't have dorms, and so I won't even get a chance to try and change to that. I'm afraid.....So absolutely and completely afraid that now, outside the safety of Prout, I'm gonna fall and fall hard.....I'm afraid that I am once again going to be looked down upon and shunned and disgraced and humiliated by my new classmates...that I will be utterly and completely alone....and that I'll lie solely for those times when I can go visit Prout, or when I get to see someone from my wonderful Highschool years.....and that the rest of my life will just be one living Hell-On-Earth, just like before...... I Don't want to be alone!!!!! I NEED people....without people....I'm nothing...I'm a pathetic waste of matter, and I have no reason to exist.... Not one is anywhere near as accepting as my family has been here at Prout....no one...... And I don't want to lose the people I have grown so close to these past 4 or 5 years....If I do...I know that part of me will just die...and I won't be able to live as I have....happy... Which brings me down to what it is I have started working on.... I would like to present to those who haven't heard yet, or have but need reminding, or have and don't need reminding and are actually getting very sick of hearing about it, I am putting together an address book for the Prouties of '05, and need help with it. I need e-mail addresses, AIM Screen names, and the person they accompany e-mailed to me @: Trunks02835@mailblocks.com If you can help me, that'd be awesome. If not, you suck, But I still love you! Remember, this is for class of 2005 members only, Please only send their information. Thanks!! Now, back to making my list with the s/n I already have. Please help if you can. And to everyone who reads this lj, member of my class or not.....Please, I'm here, talk tome if you need someone to talk to, rant to me if you need to vent, hear me when I call out for help........and know this: I Am STUCK HERE IN RI! MIGHT AS WELL USE THAT! I am pretty much telling anyone who listens that I will be a steady contact point if they need to talk too someone about anything, whether it be local news or events, school problems, whatever, I am your guy to talk to, if you want. And soon hopefully, I'll also be able to help keep you guys all updated on anything needed to be known by everyone, and to help all of you keep up with one another. Ok! I'm off now. Remember, Seniors... Graduates....Brothers and Sisters.....Barry's song, Companions on the Journey... Would you be my friend, Walking on this journey? Would you be my companion, Stand by me right or wrong? On the road to the Promised Land... Yes...in a Heartbeat..... Much Love to the Prouties of '05! I'll be talking to all of you soon!

Finally....after all of my hard work, patience, endurance, long nights, long days, depressing weeks, and times where i thought I would die.......

To the Entire Cast and Crew of Anything Goes (especially Seniors)


Congratulations on yet another magnificient success! It was amazing. Thank you for all the hard work, dedication, and for giving me one hell of a fun time! Thank you. Seniors: I know this was your last show, and I know you must all feel pretty bummed about that. Don't think of it as the end, but rather, think of it as your lasting mark on the school. Either through your smiles, your laughs, your songs and dances, in one way or another, you've inspired someone, somewhere. You've given someone a chance, a dream...You've helped someone to overcome their fears, their saddness....Most of all, you've brought a ray of pure un-adultured happiness to the lives of many. Seniors, there will be other shows, there will be other auditions, other rehearsals, other laughs, other show dates, other audiences, and more applause. So cheer up, and get some rest, for who knows when you're next audition may be, when you move on to have your name emblazoned in lights for all to see, and once again, the world will delight in seeing your smile, and hearing your voice, while you take them away from this world, and en-trance them with the music of the night.

Today I barely even made it to work because I thought for sure we weren't going to be running since it was so horrible out at 7:45AM. But then i couldn't fall asleep again and at 8:00 I realized it was too bright in my room, which made as much sense as a toaster and purple monkey making turtle wax! So I looked out the window, getting to be pretty out, called work, said we were going out afterall. I rushed through everything and got down to work as soon as possible. All morning all I could think about was last night and if I would ever see Charlotte again. (Even if the following didn't happen, I would find a way to see this girl againbefore I turned 20 3/4!!!) When we were over in newport, we saw the flag up at Rose (we have a flag down system for pickups at Rose Island.) So we got there, and who should come down onto the dock with the overnight guest but Charlotte! ^_^ So we tried saying hi and stuff, but Skip was just like a watchful grandfather, said we had a few minutes, but didn't give us privacy, silly man...
So we talked for a few seconds while looking around, and we spotted her mom up next to the light house, and she was waving her hand pointing from the island to jamestown and back. She let Charlotte come with us for one last ride over to Jamestown and back. We just sat together talking (I was surrounded by people who would never let anything I said or did fall til the day I quit). We got to Jamestown (Picked up more employees =P) and headed back to Rose. While nobody was looking (or so I thought....) We sneaked a quick kiss, our last one bafore she goes back to HOUSTON!!!!!!!! *grrrrrrrr* So she got off, and I had to watch her slowly disappear as we backed away from the dock.

Later on, when the Rose Island boat went out and picked them up, we could see the boat leave on our way to Jamestown. It was phyiscally exhausting for me to know and realize how she was leaving, and how far she was going. She left out og Logan Int. around maybe 2, and will prolly get home around 11. >.<

I'm working on an e-mail for her right now to welcome her home.

Never take what you are given for granted. 
Never give up hope.
Never forget that love is lasting.
Never say never, since we still have forever.

Okay. Charlotte is the most remarkable girl I've ever met. Bright blue eyes, shoulder length dirty-blonde hair, an incredible smile, and she thinks that I am absolutely special (no, I'm not being egotistical, she would not stop telling me how someone like me is very rare. She also kept telling me that I had very beautiful eyes. I kid you not!)

So here's how it went down today:

I worked from 8 this morning 'til bout 4:30. At maybe 10, Charlotte got on from Rose Island with her mom. We thought we had seen the last of each other yesterday. Thankfully, that wasn't the case (I never really got to say good-bye) ^_^. So, blah blah blah, we talked on the way to Newport in between my stupid little chores onboard (you know, like selling drinks and tickets and making sure everybody is ok, that kind of crap.) So yeah, we got to Newport, Charlotte got off ( !_! ) And work continued as usual, save the 7 full boatloads of people =P. so, at about 2:20, Charlotte and her mom came back onboard, we sat, held hands, talked. We get to Rose and I invite Charlotte to stay on for the next run and go for the ride, she asked her mom(who had surprised Charlotte a lot these past couple days by letting her go around with me on our date and stuff) and her mom said "yes." So Charlotte came out for the ride.I wanted more than anything to not have to keep getting up and tying the lines and stuff. So after a glorious 'nother hour, and being scared by a drunk who we probably should not have let get on the ferry in the first place (he nearly face-faulted into the gunnel trying to get on, he was so drunk), we got to Rose I., and it was time for us to say good-bye. I was really depressed about that. We didn't even really get to say good-bye at all! When we pulled into Jamestown and my now absolute FAVORITE captain came aboard, I jokingly asked him if he would drop me off at Rose and pick me up later on, and he said that he would. But, I didn't really form a plan until I got home. I got home still sad, went upstairs and had an idea. I called the ferry, and asked the captain (John) if he seriously would be willing to take me out to the island if i got permission to go out from charlotte's mom, aunt, and aunt's friend. He said yes. So I called the lighthouse, and they said yes. So I got out there at about 6:15. I got to see the keeper's apartment for the first time. We ate dinner (It was really good{chicken salad type stuff with celery, apples, pickles.....It was damn tasty}) After dinner, Charlotte and I went for a walk around the bunkers. We talked for almost and hour. Yadda yadda yadda.....(For us to know, nothing extreme, but still would rather keep that little while private.) Then, after maybe an hour and a half of talking and hand holding, we kissed each other. I found this next part to be so unbelievable, but I don't see any reason why she'd lie about anything, but she told me right before we kissed that she didn't know how to, because it was her first time. After a while we went over to the beach and sat on the rocks there. We talked some more there. We also just sat and watched some of the boats going by in the dark. I will tell you right now, the Newport bridge at night, from that island, when you are next to someone you care about, is one of THE most beautiful things you will ever see. We just sat there talking and looking out at the water. Then I had to call the ferry to come pick me up when they got a chance. So after that we went up to the lighthouse, and I started to say my good-byes to Charlotte's mom, her aunt, and their friend Kate, but then they asked me if I'd ever been up into the light. I told them yes, but never at night. So Charlotte and I went into the light tower with the light going off every 6 to 8 seconds. It was such an awesome(it's literal definition, as in awe-inspiring =P ) sight. Before we went back down, while Charlotte was starting to head down and I was still up top, I bent over and we kissed again. Now I don't care if you guys tease me or any shit like that about what I am about to say next, but I thought that that was one of the most romantic moments of my night out on the island. Okay, so then we went back down to the keeper's apartment, and I said our final good-byes(I'm gonna miss them, not just Charlotte, but her mom, Aunt  and kate too, the three of them are awesome. Her aunt is a photographer, so she took a lot of pictures, some of me and Charlotte too, but not tonight. And Kate is a school teacher in LA.) They gave us flashlights, and for some reason, a pair of binoculars (it was too dark to use them....) and we headed down towards the dock, we stopped, said "our" good-byes where we knew we couldn't be seen by her ever watchful mother =P. Then the ferry came......>.< And then i had to leave cuz there's not much you can do that you want to when there's a searchlight from a ferry shining on you and putting you in the spotlight.

And that was the end of the most perfect 4 1/2 hours of my life.....
